VILLIERSDORP, Western Cape - A man was killed and nine other people were injured, some critically, when a truck and a bakkie collided on the R43 near Villersdorp in the Overberg on Friday. Paramedics, along with the metro and fire services, found people lying around the bakkie, and both vehicles significantly damaged, ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said. One man, believed to be in his 30s, was lying a few metres from the bakkie. [OVERBERG] - Bakkie and truck collide leaving one dead, nine injured. https://t.co/L2xVRuewcV @ewnupdates @eNCA @jour_maine @SABCNewsOnline @News24_SA @_ArriveAlive @FatalMoves pic.twitter.com/zOt1sTW6Jf "Unfortunately, the man had already succumbed to his injuries. Nothing could be done for him," said Meiring. READ: Two metered taxis set alight in broad daylight in Pretoria "Nine other injured people were found on the scene. Assessments showed that their injuries ranged from moderate to critical." The cause of the accident was not yet known, he said. African News Agency